The Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) Southwest has staged a peaceful protest in Ibadan against the non-implementation of the financial autonomy for local government, legislative and judiciary arms of government. The six Southwest states comprising of Lagos, Ekiti, Ogun, Ondo, Osun and Oyo took to the streets of Ibadan on March 16, 2022, from the NLC Secretariat and proceeded to the Oyo state House of Assembly to seek the support of the lawmakers to fasten the passage of the local government financial autonomy bill into law. The NLC chairman, Oyo state, Comrade Kayode Martins while addressing workers described the current administration of the local government as absurd. Also, Comrade Abimbola Babalola, the chairman of the Nigeria Union of Local Government Employee (NULGE) Southwest, opined that the local government should serve as a starting point for whoever is interested in power. In his remark, the speaker, Oyo state house of assembly, Rt. Hon Debo Ogundoyin pledged the readiness of the lawmakers to support the implementation of the bill noting that the assembly will convene the meeting of assemblies for the realization of the bill.